<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I have a 17th season enchanter on Brell. I am currently in the difficult phase of an Enchanters life. I have a magician friend who soloes and racks up exp quite easily. I at one point, level 15, came so close to dropping my Enchanter do to frustration in my apparent inability to solo for exp. I resorted to reading many of these boards and at first was still annoyed at the apparent consensus that our class is relatively weak. Then I took a few tips from this post and a few from that post and developed my own style of play. <br>
  I also have a Necro and a Bard that I play. At first the necro pet was an awsome asset. Great DOT's for spells and life-tap. I group hunted as well with my same magician friend except he was playing a shadowknight. As we moved from the newbie area and out to multiple MOB environments I found myself more and more missing my Enchanters crowd control abilities. I soon discovered that playing my Necro for pure power was a good way to go out and raise havoc to release energy. I also discovered that playing my Enchanter was just plain fun. <br>
  I will often hunt crows for some quick exp while waiting to hook up with my buddy. When I come across another fiter I simply help out by buffing him up a little while he fights and they all appreciate quickness. My friend and I often camp a small and secluded bandit spawn when in need of money, sashes and bronze weapons, we can easily handle this do to my crowd control abilities...yes my friend has tried to solo this location and died every time.<br>
  Noticed I am rambling so I will end by saying...illusions...buffs....faction buffs....medding un-molested as a tree (so far anyways) and yes...a certain amount of raw power...keep choke and chaotic and sanity warp all loaded if the need for raw power is there...you will be amazed how much damage you can do. I usually lead with chaotic..seems to cut down on resistance to sanity...cya )<p>

<br>
Squalor 17th season Brell</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
