<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/SmallNew.gif" border="0" alt="New Message"></td><td width="50%"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>RE:Enchanters... Good or bad?? LETS ARGUE!!! =) (modified 0 times)</b> </font></td><td width="50%" align="RIGHT"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>MourneBlade</b></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Well friends, I too am an enchanter.  If you are looking for someone to complain about them, I can't.  I can only tell you this, at level 13, I can solo any level 15 warrior and come out on top. Mainly cuz you can root them, tashan them, DoT them, Root again, Chaotic feedback a couple of times, then DoT them again while they are sitting there trying to fight off your pet... Then, root one more time, DoT them, cast another pet and you can actually finish them off with your staff or dagger with your pet helping, of course when you do this you can cast color flux to stun them a while. <p>

Now one thing I will say about Enchanters is our Sense Magic/Identify line of spells... completely useless from what I can tell, but I might not have found the proper use for them unless you are looking to find out information about the item.  <p>

As a class, and I am sure most of you will agree, Enchanters are well rounded. We may have low HP's but look at our buffs.  Rune, our strength line of spells, our weaken line, etc... (as mentioned already). We are Bombs waiting to go off.  You just have to learn how to play your Enchanter, when you do, you will be happy with him.  This is my first character and I love him. I have many friends at the 50 level, and many in the teens with me.... All agree that Enchanters are the best class to play.<p>

Now, here is an example of the power we posess.  I have a friend who has a 50 enchanter.  He was camping with some friends of his and had been waiting for a spawn for around 7 hours. Another group came up to the spawn site and wanted to take the camp over.  He was challenged by a level 50 warrior.  To make it more fair, he invited the other 3 50 warriors to join in on the fight.  He killed all 4 of them without losing a bubble of life. Now tell me that isn't power.  I am not saying that EVERY enchanter out there can do that, but if you know your character and know how to use them, you can make 4 enemies turn into 1 just by the mes spells we have.  They were helpless. Anyways, Just a little story to back my claims up.  <p>

MourneBlade 13th Season Enchanter</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
