<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I am a Gnome Enchanter and I share a love of this class. Firstly I wish to state that many players are hung up on exp or who can do the most damage in a fight. This is not the class for you if that is your thing. This class is a behind the scene power house! The enchanters buffs are ment to enhance a team of players working towards a common goal, be it exp, an Item, or simply survival in a hostile zone. I feel that to many people forget that this game is based on team work! That is where the Enchanter class shine's the brightest! As with any class, the real attribute is the person on the keyboard. I have found however that to be a "good" Enchanter, one must be in constant motion, attending your team mates and controling traffic. To sit back and simply hand out "Crack" on demand is such a shame and a waist of our skills and abilities! I take pride in my Craft and when grouped, I look after the safety of myself and fello casters! the tanks must stay on target to see the battle through. I can protact myself far better then any fighter can anyway's, unless of course the battle is completely out of control. Hehe (Though they dont like to here that) <p>

Frankly the enchanter class does not lend itself well to soloing. Don't get me wrong it can be done and done well, but one must be very carefull, selective and patient!<p>

This Class has much more to offer than peopls give credit for!<p>

Take the time to examine it and learn for yourself how fun it can be)<p>

Brendelton Silvermist "Order of the luminous Blade"<br>
45th season Enchanter</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
