<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">WOOHOO!!! I agree with all of you.<p>

For the person that was having difficulty in the late teens gaining exp while watching his druid and necro friends rack up the exp by still being able to solo yellows, you aren't alone.  18 to 24 is by far the most difficult time in an enchanters career.  I have just two words for you though.  Lake Rathetear.  If you can get one of the spawns to yourself, invite one other person to come and help you keep them under control.  Watch the exp just roll in.  2 people should have no problem keeping the arena spawn under control.  You made need a third person for the small island spawn, since they spawn much faster and you run the risk of a soothe failing and then you have a real problem on your hands.  At 23, i suggest you go and try to get into a treant group in south karana.  Treants become very boring after a while.  But 23 to 30 will go by in a week or two, honestly, if you can get in a good treant group everyday.  And by the end of that time period, money is no longer really a problem.  (perfect chance to fund that jeweling career you've been meaning to start, eh?)  I'm glad you all like enchanters, and you are all very right.  The point of the game is not to hit level 50, it's to have fun while you are trying to.  Congrats to you all on understanding such a complex, yet exciting and powerful class.  Good luck to all of you.<p>

Autumn Blight, 38 Enchanter, Prexus</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
