<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Hey, I noticed most of you think the lvls 17 to 24 are the hardest...I have only one thing to say...on controlled spawns like the Aviak 2spawns in Lake Rathe, Enchanter is the absolutely best class to be for solo exp gaming. Here's what I did at these levels. From 13 to 18 I killed a monk hermit in the lake. You know the one who looks like a beggar? Thats him. After that, I got my charisma as high as I could (150 in my case..), and started charming aviak guards on eachother. You have to count on dying a few times, but after you get the hang of it it is easy. What I am saying is that you have to try to use the Enchanters own spells, not the spells that we share with the wizards, cause they are much better at them than we are. I'm not a very good writer, but I hope this makes sense. To close, I wanna say that of all pure casters, enchanters are the ones that are most usefull in a group. Many dungeons simply cant be done without one, regardless of clarity and other buffs, we are all about crowd control.<p>

